{{distinguish|Drama Centre London}} {{Infobox university |name = Drama Studio London |native_name = |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |mottoeng = |established = 1966 |closed = |type = [[Drama school]] |affiliation = |endowment = |rector = |officer_in_charge = |chairman = |chancellor = |president = |vice-president = |superintendent = |provost = |vice_chancellor = |head_label = |head = |students = 100+ |undergrad = |postgrad = |doctoral = |other = |city = [[Ealing]] |state = |province = [[London]] |country = [[England]], [[United Kingdom]] |free_label = |free = |athletics = |colours = |colors = |sports = |nickname = DSL |mascot = |website = [https://www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk/ Drama Studio London] |logo = Drama Studio London drama school official logo.jpg |footnotes = |founder = Peter Layton |faculty = |staff = |affiliations = [[Trinity College London]], [[CDET]], [[Federation of Drama Schools]], [[De Montfort University]] }}
'''Drama Studio London''' (DSL), based in [[Ealing]], [[London]], [[United Kingdom]], Accredited Drama Training. Established reputation for excellent vocational acting courses. Teaching by the profession, for the profession. A founder member of the [[Federation of Drama Schools]] accredited by [[CDMT]] validated by Trinity College London and in partnership with [[De Montfort University]]. Validated by [[Trinity College London]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.trinitycollege.co.uk/site/?id=272|title=Trinity College London - Course providers|website=www.trinitycollege.co.uk|access-date=2017-10-03}}</ref>
The school was founded in 1966 by Peter Layton<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk/about/background|title=About {{!}} Background|website=www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> out of the need for a new, more realistic approach to actor training that took account of the professional requirements and demands of the theatre for which the students were being prepared.
DSL offers both a 1 and 2<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk/full-time-courses/2-year-diploma|title=Courses {{!}} 2 Year Acting Diploma|website=www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> Year Diploma in Professional Acting as well as a BA (Hons) in Professional Acting validated by De Montfort University. Students on the 1 & 2 Year Diplomas can top up to a degree with [[Middlesex University]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk/courses/trinity-college-diploma |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-03-03 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150313210051/http://www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk/courses/trinity-college-diploma |archivedate=2015-03-13 |df= }}</ref> There are also short and part time courses<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk/short-courses|title=Short Courses|website=www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref> to choose from.
In 1995, Friends of DSL, under the Presidency of Dame [[Judi Dench]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk/the-friends|title=The Friends|website=www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk|language=en-gb|access-date=2017-10-02}}</ref>, was established in order to help provide scholarships for future students.
==Facilities== Drama Studio London's facilities:<ref>http://www.dramastudiolondon.co.uk/facilities-accommodation</ref> * The Grange Court Theatre * TV Studio * Radio Suite * 5 Rehearsal studios * Common Room * Library and computer suite
