{{Infobox comic book title <!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics--> | title = Gutter Magic | image = Gutter Magic issue 1 2016.jpg | imagesize = | noimage = yes | caption = Cover to ''Gutter Magic'' #1 (January 2016). | schedule = Monthly | format = [[Limited series (comics)|Limited series]] | publisher = [[IDW Publishing]] | date = January 2016 - April 2016 | issues = 4 | main_char_team = | writers = Rich Douek | artists = Brett Barkley | pencillers = | inkers = | letterers = | colorists = | editors = | creative_team_month = | creative_team_year = | creators = | subcat = | sort = | nonUS = | TPB = July 26, 2016 | ISBN = 1631406590 }}
'''''Gutter Magic''''' is a four part [[Limited series (comics)|limited series]] of [[comic book]]s written by Rich Douek and illustrated by Brett Barkley, published by [[IDW Publishing]] with the first part released in January 2016. All four parts were published in a trade paperback released on July 19, 2016.<ref name="trade">{{Cite web|url=http://www.comicsexperience.com/2016/07/gutter-magic-trade-paperback-now-stores/|title=Gutter Magic Trade Paperback Now in Stores!|publisher=Comics Experience|first=Meredith|last=Nudo|date=2016-07-19|accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref>
==Publication history== ''Gutter Magic'' was originally published in 2012 as a [[New York Comic Con]] exclusive. Published by Sixgun comics, it consisted as a collection of three short stories and retailed at 99c.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bleedingcool.com/2017/07/01/bleeding-in-the-gutters/|title=Bleeding In The Gutters|publisher=[[Bleeding Cool]]|first=Rich|last=Johnston|date=2017-07-01|accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bleedingcool.com/2011/10/15/nycc-debut-gutter-magic-for-99c/|title=NYCC Debut: Gutter Magic For 99c|publisher=[[Bleeding Cool]]|first=Rich|last=Johnston|date=2011-10-15|accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref>
On July 21, 2014, IDW had announced an alliance with Comics Experience, LLC, an online comics education resource and creative community, which would focus on publishing creator-owned titles by new writers. Along with the deal, four new mini-series had been announced to be released starting from January 2015 which were ''Drones'', ''Creature Cops: Special Varmint Unit'', ''Gutter Magic'' and ''Tet'', with IDW Editor and Comics Experience alum Bobby Curnow watching over the deal. Editor-In-Chief of IDW [[Chris Ryall]] said in a statement "IDW has been a strong supporter of creator-owned comics, from our very first title, 30 Days of Night, through to Locke & Key and beyond. We’re now excited to be partnering with Comics Experience to introduce the next wave of new talent to fans and the industry."<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.idwpublishing.com/idw-and-comics-experience-announce-publishing-alliance-featuring-creator-owned-books-from-new-talent/|title=IDW And Comics Experience Announce Publishing Alliance Featuring Creator-Owned Books From New Talent|publisher=[[IDW Publishing]]|date=2014-07-21|accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref>
===''Tales from the Gutter''=== In 2017, Douek launched a [[Kickstarter]] to produce ''Tales From the Gutter: A Gutter Magic Anthology''. The comic will expand upon the stories in the original series and include what couldn't be told previously.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.geek.com/comics/interview-with-comic-creator-rich-douek-on-returning-to-the-world-of-gutter-magic-1706514/|title=Interview with Comic Creator Rich Douek on Returning to the World of Gutter Magic|publisher=[[Geek.com]]|first=Keenan|last=McClelland|date=2017-07-08|accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref>
==Plot== Set in modern-day [[New York City]] where [[World War II]] had been fought with magic and wizards are the elitists, the series follows Cinder Byrnes, a member of a wealthy family of magic users, who was born without powers and his journey to learn how to cast spells.
==Reception== Reviews for the series had generally been positive, with review aggregator website Comic Book Roundup giving the series an average score of 8.0 out of 10.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://comicbookroundup.com/comic-books/reviews/idw-publishing/gutter-magic|title=Gutter Magic|publisher=Comic Book Roundup|accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref>
===Sales=== According to [[ICv2]], issue #1 was one of the top 300 comics sold of January, 2016, with approximately 4,577 copies sold,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://icv2.com/articles/markets/view/33653/top-300-comics-actual-january-2016|title=TOP 300 COMICS ACTUAL--JANUARY 2016|publisher=''[[ICv2]]''|date=2016-02-08|accessdate=2017-07-14}}</ref> making it the first comic by Comics Experience to ever appear on the list.<ref name="trade"/>
